##The disease warning rises to the highest, South Korea will test "new world" Church all members

I-CAIJING

South Korea has passed the government epidemic prevention departments can control the epidemic independently stage, now has entered the whole society to cooperate with the epidemic prevention critical period. According to the relevant departments of the exercise, before March 3 will be whether South Korea can effectively control the outbreak of the time window

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Workers disinfect a market in Taegu, South Korea, Feb. 23. FIGURE / method new

By Cai Tingyi and Wang Xiaofeng, CAIJING reporters

Editor | Hao Zhou

Secret Churches, closed homes for the elderly, the military, suspected cases of unwillingness to cooperate with epidemic prevention, epidemic prevention commanders who are members of invisible secret churches... Epidemic Prevention Textbook Style challenges have appeared in South Korea since February 20, as a result, the number of confirmed cases has doubled in just a few days, and South Korea has suddenly become the worst affected region outside COVID-19, forcing the containment based epidemic prevention policy to seek disaster reduction.

In South Korea, the outbreak began to heat up on February 21, with an increase of 100 cases on the day of diagnosis, followed by 229 cases on the 22nd, 169 on the 23rd, 231 on the 24th and 144 on the 25th. As of 9:00 a.m. on the 26th, South Korea had 169 new confirmed cases, bringing the total to 1,146, and 11 deaths nationwide, according to a report from the central disaster and Safety Countermeasures Department, among them, 944 cases were confirmed in Daegu city and kyeongsang-do-gyeongdo county, accounting for 82.3% of the total number of confirmed infections in South Korea.

With the number of cases rapidly rising, South Korea's epidemic prevention authorities were too late to investigate and block the source of infection in each case.

South Korean President Moon jae-in declared a state of emergency Wednesday, raising the level of infectious disease alert from "alert" to the highest level of "serious" . "please avoid undue panic and at the same time trust in the measures taken by the government, " Moon said, adding that the next few days would be a critical period for epidemic prevention. Chung Sye-kyun, the prime minister in charge of disaster response, arrived in Taegu at 6 pm on the 25th and is expected to stay in Taegu until the 29th, depending on the situation, to decide whether to extend the command.

This is South Korea since the 2009 H1N1 flu, once again issued the highest level of infectious disease alert, the government in accordance with statutory standards can be issued at any time to suspend schools, prohibit group activities and other emergency orders. In view of the rapid warming of the epidemic, the South Korean government has announced that the national kindergarten, primary and secondary schools and other schools at all levels of the new school year from March 2 to March 9. According to the relevant departments, February 23 to March 3 will be whether South Korea can effectively control the outbreak of the time window.

The rapid rise in the epidemic in South Korea is mainly due to two clusters of infection, especially in the fourth-largest city, Taegu, where 458 church-related cases have been reported as of the 24th. The other source of infection is cheongsang-do-do-gyeongbodo-gyeongdo-gyeongdo-gyeongdo-gyeongdo-gyeongnam hospital, there have been 112 cases so far. Because North Gyeongsang Province is home to Lee Man-Hee, the founder of the New World Church, and members of the Church attended the funeral of the founder's brother at the hospital a few weeks ago, the Center for Disease Control and Prevention, part of the South Korean Ministry of Health and Welfare, concluded that the hospital's infection also came from the church.

As the infection floor of Nant-le-Grand hospital is mainly for the elderly and the virus has spread rapidly to the hospital's closed psychiatric inpatient building, 99 of the 102 patients in the inpatient building were confirmed, deaths have also been concentrated in hospital infections, with at least five cases reported as of February 25.

Kim Dong-hyun, an epidemiologist at Hanlin medical school in South Korea, said that South Korea has passed the stage where the government's epidemic prevention department can control the epidemic independently, and now it has entered a critical period when the whole society must cooperate in the epidemic prevention.

"Case 31" and the controversial church

"The 31st confirmed case is a woman born in 1959. " The announcement of the outbreak by the Korean Center for Disease Control and Prevention (KCDC) on February 18 updated the number of confirmed cases as usual, the first record of patient exposure was "still under investigation. "

The next day, there were 13 new cases in former president Park Chung-hee's hometown, and in the fourth largest cities of Taegu and North Gyeongsang Province. Investigations revealed that the sources were all from the 31st case. To the surprise of South Korea's Disease Control Agency, it was this case that began to multiply the number of diagnoses that followed.

According to the investigation, the 31st patient has been in and out of the local clinic since 7 February due to the car accident. She has had fever since 10 February, tested on 17 and tested positive on 18 February. South Korean media say doctors at the clinic have advised her to be screened, but she has been turned down. Unexpectedly, she became a "super-spreader" . After showing symptoms, she attended church services four times and had contact with more than 1,160 people. South Korea's epidemic prevention system has since faced severe challenges.

Investigators later found that before the diagnosis, the "31st case" had attended a gathering of 1,000 people at the controversial New World Church in Taegu and had made multiple trips to public places, with the exception of the 33rd case, which was treated by medical staff at her hospital, almost all of the other confirmed cases of infection have been church-related. The ninth death, newly announced on February 25th, is also believed to have come into contact with church officials.

According to the survey, infected "new world" Church members, mainly February 7-10 and 14-18 symptoms, the Korean Center for Disease Control and Prevention concluded that church worship may be the main occasion for the spread of the virus.

The church, which has at least 210,000 members and more than 1,000 strongholds in South Korea, tends to hide its activities from the church and its family members. "New World" Church in the early reluctant to cooperate with the epidemic prevention, the submission of the list of believers and contact information is not complete, some media pointed out that the Church asked believers to receive the epidemic prevention phone calls to deny participation in activities misleading epidemic prevention personnel. Epidemic Prevention officials later said that if the church does not cooperate will take legal action.

Moon, in particular, said after an emergency meeting on Feb. 23 that the government would close Xintiandi's churches across the country and conduct a full investigation of believers. He personally visited Daegu on the 25th and presided over the Epidemic Prevention Conference, he pointed out that the key to control the epidemic in the speed and time, and hope that the turning point of the epidemic will come soon. The move comes after the South Korean government declared Taegu and kyeongsang-do-gyeongju "Special Management Area for Infectious Diseases" .

South Korea's Central Disaster Safety Countermeasures Headquarters on February 25, said the government will "new heaven and earth" Church members to test for new coronavirus, and at any time public test results.

The Xintiandi outbreak also included the military, where a soldier in Jeju Island was infected after leaving for a holiday on February 20 to meet his girlfriend in Taegu. The South Korean Army, Navy and air force have infected 11 people, at least 7,700 people have been quarantined, and South Korea and the United States are considering scaling back the joint military exercises scheduled for March 9 because of the outbreak. South Korea's Ministry of Defense on the 25th because a photographer found suspected symptoms, announced the temporary closure of briefing room.

Ordinary people's lives change

In addition to announcing a one week delay, the Daegu city government also ordered 1,324 kindergartens in the city to close and 252 geriatric medical facilities to restrict access for outsiders. In addition to the cancellation of major events held in Daegu city, many government departments have also changed to work from home.

"We felt as if the centre of the city had been hit by a bomb and there was no one there... people on the road were wearing masks and many places needed to be taken to get their temperature, " Meredith Khanloo, an American who lives near the New World Church in Taegu, told CAIJING. Many South Koreans see the new World Church as a negative force in society and find it uncomfortable for devotees to preach the Gospel on the road, she said, after 13 years in Taegu, but before this outbreak, most people chose to ignore them.

The church was founded in 1984 by Lee Man-Hee, who claimed to have a "non-bad body" and was known for his controversial methods of secretly proselytizing, in which believers were asked to infiltrate other churches without being identified. Believers believe that Lee Man-Hee is the second coming of Christ, that the church is the true heir, and that when Judgment Day comes it will lead them to heaven.

To the surprise of the outside world, on February 24, Daegu western district health officials involved in the main epidemic area infected with the virus, confirmed after he admitted that he is also a "new world" Church followers. The official was in charge of the region's overall epidemic prevention policy, and 50 staff members of the clinic were ordered to return home immediately to quarantine themselves after the diagnosis.

Tens of thousands of people have signed a petition calling for the church to be disbanded, but a church spokesman dismissed the church as a victim and accused outsiders of tarnishing it. However, the church later changed its attitude and reached an agreement with the government to hand over the names and contact details of all its members, especially those who attended church events in Taegu in january-february this year, to cooperate with the government in conducting virus tests.

Ms. Park, who lives in Seoul and works as a chinese-korean translator, angrily told Caijing that the new coronaviruses' epidemic in South Korea was caused by "Xintiandi" believers. "those people are not in their right mind. We were not worried about the new coronavirus, but now the situation has completely changed and we are beginning to worry and even feel uneasy. " Ms. Park's son just went through graduation on Feb. 14, at the time, South Korea had no idea of the new coronavirus epidemic.

Meredith, who has two children, expressed concern that she and many South Korean mothers will not be able to get their children to school on time for the new school day unless she believes the epidemic is under control, "mothers are very concerned that their children will be isolated or treated in hospital. "

To contain the outbreak as soon as possible, the central government is preparing a new budget to assist the governments of Taegu and North Gyeongsang Province to implement an outbreak blockade, "tight network" to block further community transmission.

In addition, despite the recent increase in mask production by domestic manufacturers, which is expected to reach 11 million tablets per day, the government decided to restrict exports from Feb. 26 due to a shortage of supplies due to high domestic demand.

China and South Korea enjoy close ties and face the challenge of how to prevent epidemics together. The South Korean government has allocated 5 billion won (28.88 million yuan) for 14 days of isolation and the distribution of face masks to Chinese students as universities open and 38,000 Chinese students return to the country.

On the Internet, there have even been suggestions that a large number of South Korean tourists have taken refuge in Qingdao, China, by plane. The cultural information officer of the South Korean Embassy in China, Kim man-soo, told Caijing that it is not accurate to say that they have come to China to escape the epidemic, there are a lot of regular travelers between China and South Korea, and both countries are now fighting the spread of the epidemic.

To show the friendship between China and South Korea, South Korean President Moon jae-in and Chinese President Xi Jinping spoke on February 21 to express South Korea's goodwill in assisting China in fighting the epidemic. The talks also confirmed that high-level talks between China and South Korea will be held as scheduled, president Xi will visit South Korea in the first half of this year.
